metadata.name: Tour de l'Horloge du palais de la Cité
metadata.description: The Clock Tower (Tour de l’Horloge) was built between 1350 and 1353 and is at 47 metres the Conciergerie‘s tallest tower. Since 1371 it has housed the remarkable clock whose purpose was to help Parisians to regulate theirs activities during the day and night.
